"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386801","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-06","<p /> <p>Estimates of the number and proportion of children in relative and absolute low-income are published in the National Statistics Households Below Average Income (HBAI) series.</p><p> </p><p>Analysis by region is presented as three-year averages as single-year estimates are considered too volatile. Figures are presented in financial year estimates and are available up to 2013/14.</p><p> </p><p>The latest publication is available at the link below: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/households-below-average-income-19941995-to-20132014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/households-below-average-income-19941995-to-20132014</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-06T14:14:33.007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386801/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386801/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386801/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-30","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many children in the West Midlands region live in poverty.","false","Biography information for Mr David Winnick","Walsall North","Mr David Winnick","4927"
