"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386229","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-03","<p>Statistics on new house building completions in England, London and in each London borough, including Enfield, are published in the Department's live tables 253 (annual) and 253a (quarterly), which are available at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-house-building" target="_blank">http://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/live-tables-on-house-building</a></p><p> </p><p>These figures exclude other sources of housing supply such as conversions.<br><br>These statistics are not available by parliamentary constituency.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-03T13:17:59.107Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386229/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386229/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386229/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-29","Housing: Construction","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the housing completion rates were in (a) England, (b) London, (c) Enfield and (d) Enfield North constituency in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","4671"
