"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386231","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-03","<p>The number of bedrooms required by households on local authority waiting list are published in the Department’s data set ‘Local authority housing statistics data returns’, table C, which is available at the following link.<br><br><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/local-authority-housing-statistics-data-returns-for-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/local-authority-housing-statistics-data-returns-for-2013-to-2014</a></p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-03T13:16:02.703Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386231/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386231/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386231/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-29","Social Rented Housing: Enfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many households are on the social housing waiting list in the London Borough of Enfield; and how many of those households require a (a) one bedroom, (b) two bedroom and (c) three bedroom property.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","4673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386232","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-06","<p>Statistics on home ownership for London and the London Borough of Enfield, based on Census 2011 data, are published by the Office for National Statistics, and are available at the following link.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/census/2011/ks402ew" target="_blank">https://www.nomisweb.co.uk/census/2011/ks402ew</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-06T14:47:41.12Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386232/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386232/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386232/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-29","Owner Occupation: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what proportion of households were owner-occupied in (a) London and (b) Enfield in (i) 2010-11, (ii) 2011-12, (iii) 2012-13, (iv) 2013-14 and (v) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","4614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386233","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-06","<p>Over 300 Jobcentre Plus Work Coaches are based in 149 upper-tier local authorities and are working with their troubled families teams to support delivery of the programme’s employment outcomes.</p><p> </p><p>The only upper-tier local authorities without dedicated Jobcentre Plus staff are the City of London, Isles of Scilly and Rutland. These three areas have the lowest numbers of troubled families.</p><p> </p><p>These Jobcentre Plus staff work closely with local services in addressing the multiple barriers to employment faced by troubled families, including mental health problems, substance misuse and low skills.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","4557","2015-07-06T14:51:09.767Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386233/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386233/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386233/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-29","Families: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what role Jobcentre Plus plays in the referral of benefit claimants to participate in the Troubled Families programme.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","4558"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386234","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-06","<p>The <em>Understanding Troubled Families </em>report, published in 2014 and based on a sample of 8,447 troubled families, found that 49% were lone parent households, compared to 17% in the wider population.</p><p> </p><p>Further demographic detail of the families in the original Troubled Families Programme (2012-15) will become available from its independent national evaluation later this year.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark",,"2015-07-06T14:53:03.157Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386234/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386234/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386234/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-29","Families: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many and what proportion of participants in the Troubled Families programme to date have been single parents.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","4559"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386235","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-06","<p>Over 300 Jobcentre Plus Work Coaches are based in 149 upper-tier local authorities and are working with their troubled families teams to support delivery of the programme’s employment outcomes.</p><p> </p><p>The only upper-tier local authorities without dedicated Jobcentre Plus staff are the City of London, Isles of Scilly and Rutland. These three areas have the lowest numbers of troubled families.</p><p> </p><p>These Jobcentre Plus staff work closely with local services in addressing the multiple barriers to employment faced by troubled families, including mental health problems, substance misuse and low skills.</p>","Tunbridge Wells","Greg Clark","4558","2015-07-06T14:51:09.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386235/answer","Biography information for Greg Clark","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386235/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386235/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-29","Families: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, in which local authorities have local jobcentre plus staff been appointed to assist in the delivery of the Troubled Families programme.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","4557"
