"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386318","Scotland Office","false","2015-07-06","<p>The members of the Scotland Office and Office of the Advocate General’s Joint Management Board are:</p><p>Secretary of State for Scotland, Rt Hon David Mundell MP;</p><p>Parliamentary Under Secretary of State for Scotland, Lord Dunlop;</p><p>Advocate General for Scotland, Lord Keen of Elie QC;</p><p>Francesca Osowska, Director of the Scotland Office;</p><p>Michael Chalmers, Director of the Office of the Advocate General;</p><p>Ruaraidh Macniven, Legal Secretary to the Advocate General for Scotland;</p><p>Helena Gray, Deputy Director, Scotland Office;</p><p>Graeme Bissett, Non-Executive Director;</p><p>Joyce Cullen, Non-Executive Director;</p><p>Shonaig Macpherson, Non-Executive Director;</p><p>Edward Adams, Non-Executive Director.</p><p> </p><p>Four members of the management Board are women.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-07-06T12:12:14.6Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386318/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386318/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386318/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-06-29","Scotland Office: Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, who the members of the management board of his Department are; and how many of those members are women.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","4627"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386319","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-07","<p>The Department for Transport Board consists of the Department’s Ministers, the non-executive Board Members and the senior executive team of the Department and these are list below for 1<sup>st</sup> June 2015. There are currently five members who are women.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Ministers</strong></p></td><td></td></tr><tr><td><p>Secretary of State</p></td><td><p>Rt Hon Patrick McLoughlin MP</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Parliamentary Under Secretary of State</p></td><td><p>Robert Goodwill MP</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Parliamentary Under Secretary of State</p></td><td><p>Claire Perry MP</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Parliamentary Under Secretary of State</p></td><td><p>Andrew Jones MP</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Parliamentary Under Secretary of State</p></td><td><p>Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Non-Executive Board Members</strong></p></td><td></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lead Non-Executive Board Member</p></td><td><p>Ed Smith</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Non-Executive</p></td><td><p>Richard Brown</p></td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td></tr><tr><td><p>Non-Executive</p></td><td><p>Mary Reilly</p></td></tr><tr><td></td><td></td></tr><tr><td><p>Non-Executive</p></td><td><p>Dame Colette Bowe</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Executive Members</strong></p></td><td></td></tr><tr><td><p>Permanent Secretary</p></td><td><p>Philip Rutnam</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Director General</p></td><td><p>Lucy Chadwick</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Director General</p></td><td><p>Jonathan Moor</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Director General</p></td><td><p>Clare Moriarty</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Director General</p></td><td><p>David Prout</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Acting Director General</p></td><td><p>John Dowie</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-07T10:01:38.377Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386319/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386319/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386319/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Department for Transport: Management","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, who the members of the management board of his Department are; and how many of those members are women.","false","Biography information for Angela Crawley","Lanark and Hamilton East","Angela Crawley","4628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386320","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>There is currently £20 million annually available for the next three years from the Regional Air Connectivity Fund. The Government has already provided £3.4 million to support both the Dundee to London Stansted route and the Newquay to Gatwick route through public service obligations in 2014/15 and 2015/16 and has committed a further £2million over this and the next three financial years to support these routes.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to this the Government undertook earlier this year an initial application stage for airlines to bid for start-up aid funding. The Government will announce after the July Budget how we will take this forward.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-02T11:41:33.9Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386320/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386320/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386320/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Regional Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the amount of Regional Air Connectivity funding that will be made available in each of the next three years.","false","Biography information for Chris Law","Dundee West","Chris Law","4537"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386321","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>HS2 Ltd’s aim is for all trees to be UK grown, if possible.　 Until the procurement process has been complete it is not possible to confirm the actual countries from which trees will be sourced.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-02T11:24:42.33Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386321/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386321/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386321/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, from which countries the trees required for ecological mitigation planting for High Speed 2 will be sourced.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","4640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386322","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>It is not expected that any ancient woodland areas will be utilised for temporary works. HS2 Ltd are working to ensure that any such impacts on ancient woodland, if identified, are removed as part of the detailed design process.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-02T11:32:35.563Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386322/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386322/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386322/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which ancient woodlands in which areas are currently planned for destruction for temporary works associated with High Speed 2.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","4642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386323","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>Procurement of trees will follow Royal Assent. 　HS2 Ltd are working closely with the Forestry Commission and Growers Associations to ensure that tree procurement and supply is undertaken in accordance to the specification and programme described in the Environmental Statement.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-02T11:28:38.507Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386323/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386323/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386323/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of the trees required for ecological mitigation planting for High Speed 2 have been procured.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","4641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386324","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>A Supplementary Environmental Statement relating to the High Speed Rail (London – West Midlands) Bill will be deposited in Parliament, and in local authority offices and libraries in affected areas, on 13<sup>th</sup> July 2015. It will also be published online on gov.uk on that date. The consultation period will run from 13<sup>th</sup> July until 28th August 2015, a period of 47 days.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-02T11:36:23.853Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386324/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386324/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386324/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the supplementary environmental statement for High Speed 2 will be published; and how long the consultation period for that document will be.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","4643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386325","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-07","<p>It is the responsibility of the developers, working with Network Rail, to undertake any feasibility study, cost analysis or modifications necessary to the Elstree rail tunnels to achieve W10 gauge clearance. This forms part of the required Rail Related Works set out in the Conditions attached to the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government’s approval of the planning application for the Radlett Strategic Rail Freight Terminal.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","4620","2015-07-07T14:36:30.343Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386325/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386325/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386325/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Railways: Elstree","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether a feasibility study has been undertaken on modifications to the Elstree rail tunnels; and whether his Department has undertaken a cost analysis on those modifications.","false","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","4550"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386326","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-07","<p>It is the responsibility of the developers, working with Network Rail, to undertake any feasibility study, cost analysis or modifications necessary to the Elstree rail tunnels to achieve W10 gauge clearance. This forms part of the required Rail Related Works set out in the Conditions attached to the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government’s approval of the planning application for the Radlett Strategic Rail Freight Terminal.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","4550","2015-07-07T14:36:30.44Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386326/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386326/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386326/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Railways: Radlett","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has made an assessment of the capacity of the Elstree rail tunnels to accommodate rail freight trains for the proposed Radlett rail freight terminal.","false","Biography information for Oliver Dowden","Hertsmere","Oliver Dowden","4620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386327","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-07","<p>The line between Wolverhampton and Telford is not currently funded for electrification. We are awaiting the publication by Network Rail of its Electrification Route Utilisation Strategy, which has looked at this route, among others, as candidates to be electrified. The Government expects to publish its next Rail Investment Strategy for 2019-2024 in July 2017.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-07T11:07:06.733Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386327/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386327/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386327/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Telford-Wolverhampton Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to ensure the electrification of the train line between Wolverhampton and Telford.","false","Biography information for Lucy Allan","Telford","Lucy Allan","4685"
