://data.parliament.uk/resources/386328/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386328/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386328/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, which ancient woodlands are under discussion with Natural England to be added to the ancient woodland inventory of Phase 1 of High Speed 2.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","4612"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386329","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>The electrification of Manchester to Preston comprises many projects.　 For example, Network Rail are currently enlarging the Farnworth Tunnel to enable electrification between Manchester to Preston and that project will be completed by October 2015.　 The majority of elements of the other projects have advanced to at least GRIP 3 single option development and only a very small number remain to be finalised. This is expected to be achieved for these elements by the end of August 2015.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-02T11:53:53.497Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386329/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386329/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386329/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Railways: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of  Network Rail's progress on delivering the Manchester to Preston electrification project; when he expects that project to be completed; and whether that project has advanced to GRIP 3 single option selection.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386330","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>In the last 12 months, a Minister chaired Performance Delivery Group meetings on 13 October 2014, 10 December 2014, 20 January 2015 and 24 March 2015; and I was that Minister.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-07-02T12:01:19.207Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386330/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386330/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386330/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Railways: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on which dates a Minister in his Department has chaired the Performance Delivery Group in the last 12 months; and which Minister chaired each such meeting.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386331","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-07","<p>The intention is for all trees to be UK grown, if possible. On the advice of the Forestry Commission and others, one third of the seed to come from the UK.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-07T11:15:49.72Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386331/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386331/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386331/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of trees used for ecological mitigation planting for High Speed 2 will be sourced from the UK.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","4611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386332","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-07","<p>HS2 Ltd has not challenged the classification of additional woodlands. 　HS2 Ltd have provided survey information and heritage information assessments of all of the additional ancient woodlands suggested to Natural England by the Woodland Trust and other stakeholders. 　This has enabled Natural England to come to their own informed conclusions about which ancient woodlands should be added to the inventory.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-07-07T11:27:52.987Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386332/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386332/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386332/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for what reasons HS2 Ltd is challenging the classification of the additional woods to be added to the ancient woodland inventory; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","4613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386333","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>The incoming Chair of Network Rail will receive £500,000 for four days work per week in the first two years of appointment and then £300,000 for a minimum two-day week during the next two years. This is comparable to the pay of the incumbent Chair on a pro-rata basis. This is a contract for services and not a contract of employment. There will be no pension benefit and no bonus. In total the incoming Chair’s pay will be less than his overall salary package at Transport for London.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The role of Chair at Network Rail is a very significant leadership and delivery role. It comes with the challenge of recommending proposals for re-profiling the enhancements programme and taking clear responsibility for delivering it, at a time of strong passenger growth on the operational railway.</p><p> </p>","Derbyshire Dales","Mr Patrick McLoughlin",,"2015-07-02T15:50:37.43Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386333/answer","Biography information for Sir Patrick McLoughlin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386333/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386333/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Network Rail","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the annual salary will be of the incoming Chair of Network Rail.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386334","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>I regularly meet with the Prime Minister to discuss a wide range of transport issues.</p><p> </p>","Derbyshire Dales","Mr Patrick McLoughlin",,"2015-07-02T15:35:33.063Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386334/answer","Biography information for Sir Patrick McLoughlin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386334/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386334/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Railways: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he first  held a substantive conversation with the Prime Minister on cost overruns on Network Rail's electrification programme.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386335","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>I, Ministers and officials regularly meet to discuss the Midland Main Line, North of England and Great Western Programmes.</p>","Derbyshire Dales","Mr Patrick McLoughlin",,"2015-07-02T15:31:39.817Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386335/answer","Biography information for Sir Patrick McLoughlin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386335/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386335/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Railways","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on what dates (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department attended meetings of (i) the Midland Main Line Programme Board, (ii) the North of England Programme Board and (iii) the Great Western Programme Board in the last six months; and which Ministers and officials were present at each such meeting.","false","Biography information for Lilian Greenwood","Nottingham South","Lilian Greenwood","4665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386336","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>The Traffic Commissioner for Wales is a joint appointment with that of the Traffic Commissioner for the West Midlands. There is an insufficient volume of operators to justify a separate Welsh commissioner. All public inquires for Welsh operators are heard in Wales.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-02T11:57:12.7Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386336/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386336/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386336/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Traffic Commissioners: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make it his policy to appoint a Traffic Commissioner for Wales who is based in Wales.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","4720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386337","Department for Transport","false","2015-07-02","<p>Driving licences displaying the Union flag will be issued to drivers in England, Scotland and Wales at the same time. The date for this will be announced in due course.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-07-02T13:05:27.88Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386337/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386337/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386337/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-06-29","Driving: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what date has been appointed for the introduction of the Union flag on all  driving licences issued to drivers in (a) England, (b) Scotland and (c) Wales.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","4721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386338","Women and Equalities","false","2015-07-06","<p>A progress report on the Equality Strategy was published on 22 May 2012. In relation to Section 3 of that strategy, the Department for Communities and Local Government is undertaking a number of initiatives in support of this aim. These include the Delivering Differently in Neighbourhoods programme, which is providing 24 local authorities with grants to redesign services so that they are delivered at neighbourhood level, and the Our Place programme, which is putting the local community at the heart of decision making by bringing together local councillors, public servants, businesses and the community to revolutionise the way the neighbourhood works.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2015-07-06T16:20:31.953Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386338/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386338/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386338/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2015-06-29","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what steps she is taking to implement the conclusions of the Equality Strategy - Building a Fairer Britain, published in December 2010, particularly those in Section 3 of that strategy involving the devolution of power to local authorities.","false","Biography information for Mr Douglas Carswell","Clacton","Mr Douglas Carswell","4684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386339","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-03","<p>Housing Benefit claims data, including details of claims from people aged between 18 and 21 and the numbers affected by the removal of the spare room subsidy is published and can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk</a></p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html</a></p><p> </p><p>Please note the data relating to the removal of the spare room policy only shows the impact for those who remain entitled to Housing Benefit. The effect upon those who are no longer entitled to Housing Benefit is not available.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","4679 ; 4700","2015-07-03T12:09:59.957Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386339/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386339/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386339/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-29","Housing Benefit: Enfield","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people aged between 18 and 21 in the London Borough of Enfield were in receipt of housing benefit in (a) 2010-11, (b) 2011-12, (c) 2012-13, (d) 2013-14 and (e) 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","4680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386340","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-03","<p /> <p>Estimates of the number and proportion of children in relative and absolute low-income are published in the National Statistics Households Below Average Income (HBAI) series.</p><p> </p><p>Due to small sample sizes figures for Enfield and Enfield North constituency are not available as robust estimates cannot be produced for local level geographies. However, HBAI does provide 3-year average estimates of the number and proportion of children in relative and absolute low-income for both England and London.</p><p> </p><p>Analysis by region is presented as three-year averages as single-year estimates are considered too volatile. Figures are presented in financial year estimates and are available up to 2013/14.</p><p> </p><p>The latest publication is available at the link below: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/households-below-average-income-19941995-to-20132014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/households-below-average-income-19941995-to-20132014</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-03T13:46:55.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386340/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386340/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386340/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-29","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many children were in (a) relative and (b) absolute poverty  in (i) England, (ii) London, (iii) Enfield and (iv) Enfield North constituency in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","4678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386341","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-03","<p /> <p>Housing Benefit claims data, including details of claims from people aged between 18 and 21 and the numbers affected by the removal of the spare room subsidy is published and can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/" target="_blank">https://stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk</a></p><p>Guidance on how to extract the information required can be found at:</p><p><a href="https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html" target="_blank">https://sw.stat-xplore.dwp.gov.uk/webapi/online-help/Getting-Started---SuperWEB2.html</a></p><p> </p><p>Please note the data relating to the removal of the spare room policy only shows the impact for those who remain entitled to Housing Benefit. The effect upon those who are no longer entitled to Housing Benefit is not available.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","4680 ; 4700","2015-07-03T12:09:59.85Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386341/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386341/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386341/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-29","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in work were claiming housing benefit in May (a) 2010 and (b) 2015 in (i) England, (ii) London, (iii) Enfield and (iv) Enfield North constituency.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","4679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386342","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-02","<p /> <p>The Department does not disclose commercially sensitive information.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-07-02T14:58:28.007Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386342/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386342/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386342/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-29","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department has budgeted for IT consultancy support related to universal credit in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","4584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386343","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-07","<p>It is right that we conduct research to ensure the public understand the rationale and impact of policies.</p><p> </p><p>The Department spent £271,849 on a suite of commissioned research evaluating the effect of the benefit cap. Reports were published over a period between July 2013 to December 2014. All the spending was after the cap had been implemented.</p><p> </p><p>In addition to the commissioned research, DWP published departmental analysis of the effects of the cap in “Benefit Cap: Analysis of outcomes of capped claimants”, and also publishes quarterly Official Statistics showing details of the capped caseload.</p><p> </p><p>Public polling and focus groups typically form one element of research. Specific cost breakdowns are not available.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","4596","2015-07-07T10:08:14.42Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386343/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386343/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386343/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-29","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how much his Department spent on research evaluating the effect of the benefit cap (a) before and (b) after that cap's implementation.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","4597"
