"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386349","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-01","<p /> <p>The Government’s commitment to reduce welfare spending was set out in its election manifesto. Further details will be given in due course.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-01T14:10:57.13Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386349/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386349/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386349/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-29","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect of reductions in the welfare budget on children with sensory loss.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","4542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386350","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-02","<p /> <p>I refer the Rt. Hon. Member to the answer I gave on 23 June 2015 to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-15/2538/" target="_blank">UIN2538</a>.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-02T14:47:17.613Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386350/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386350/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386350/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-29","Housing Benefit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will increase the amount of discretionary housing payment funding to local authorities after the reduction of the household benefit cap.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","4585"
