"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386006","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-01","<p>The information requested can be found using the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2014</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","4452","2015-07-01T12:22:43.443Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386006/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386006/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386006/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-26","Housing Benefit: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of the total value of payment of housing benefit was for properties in London in the most recent period for what figures are available.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","4453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386007","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-01","<p /> <p>The information requested is published and available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistics-tabulation-tool" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistics-tabulation-tool</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users is available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance</a></p><p> </p><p>Proportions can then be calculated using the published figures for all entitled against those in receipt of Carer’s Allowance.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-01T13:39:13.11Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386007/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386007/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386007/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-26","Carer's Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, (a) how many people were eligible to receive and (b) how many and what proportion of people were in receipt of carer's allowance in each local authority area on the latest date for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","4448"
